task.summary: Default task

Added a MapEdit class (and interior classes) which functions as a Tab for editing a map Added a TabPane and tabs, which will be where most of the editor's stuff is Currently a MapEdit tab can be opened but no content really appears as I haven't made a map viewer yet Renamed PxPackMap class to PxPack Added LAST_UPDATED_STRING for last date of code update FileChooser, not DirectoryChooser, is now used to navigate to mod base Title now incorporates mod path Added functionality to mapList context menu

Added Changeable interface Moved Utilities out of util package Updated some javadoc Removed jetbrains annotations Renamed MapEdit class to MapEditTab Gave PxPack and MapEditTab equals() and hashCode() Changed Color in PxPack to use javafx.scene.paint.Color rather than awt.Color Added enums for menu item indexes in arrays Now uses Preferences class to store settings, though the JRE can't create a key in the Windows registry due to a bug (that will hopefully be fixed with Java 9) Map ListView actions are bound in bindActionsToMapListView() now, not addMapsToListView() Added Reload functionality, which reloads entire mod
Side note - I'll probably start increasing version numbers once it has legitimate functionality, like at least map viewing

Massive changes - I should commit more often Edits maps (no saving, not for a while) Loads script files (though this may be broken... - doesn't always show a script in the tab) Save and save all Created class for storing methods (for later undo/redo system) Uses Preferences class to store config options ResourceBundle for strings Logging class Store tiles as 2D int array now instead of 1D byte ArrayList Removed math utilities, put the javafx-related utilities into JavaFXUtil class Using Java1.8 instead of 1.7 now since I needed the Optional class for the map layer resize dialog (maybe I can find a replacement and switch back) Probably other stuff (it's been almost 2 weeks since the last commit! - I swear I'll be better about it!) Still a lot more to do - massive TODO comment in KeroEdit class

Mainly refactoring and efficiency New Actions menu, with option to run the game Can drag to set tiles in map (choppy/slow however - probably because I need to use Tasks more) Single Canvas for map layers instead of a pane and three canvases Canvas for tileset viewer Made better use of Properties in the TIleEditTab Next will probably be some work on the entity editor

TileEditTab improvements
Can display tile types/attributes Removed drag to add tiles since it was slow - need to use Tasks more or something (or maybe switch back to StackPane + 3 canvas) Seems to have high memory usage so I'll look into that

Primarily more changes to MapEditTab SplitPanes in the tile editing tab (between map and tileset and tileset and selected tile) Singular settings pane for selected layer, displayed layers, and tile type display (above the main tab pane) Tile types are on separate canvas with visibility toggled Refactoring for speed and ease of use Individual map settings pane temporarily disabled as I figure out where to put it Updated specs/parsing on PXPACK
Moved ScriptEditTab out of MapEditTab Added support for opening fix.pxeve and island.pxeve (and an option for explain.pxeve that doesn't yet do anything) Refactoring and reorganization

Tons more stuff and I need to commit more often Undo/redo system & basic framework for saving files Created PxAttr management system as they are shared among maps so updates in one map need to be reflected in others Refactoring Can pop out tileset (double click) - still needs some improvements Basics of an executable patcher JSON files for strings located in executables and pxeve commands + args JSON parser Licensed under Apache 2.0 Creates an assist folder when a new mod is loaded (disabled for now as there was a bug with invalid paths) License prompt when the program starts if the user hasn't already agreed to it (disabled for now as for some reason program would immediately exit w/o prompt) Proper Shift-JIS encoding
Fixed readme to have accurate last update date
SettingsPane in MapEditTab turned into context menu Right click on map pane to resize current layer or change bg color; SettingsPane also removed File and code cleanup Stub for tile attributes
Added waffle button Under Actions menu - prints a picture of a waffle

Various drawing additions Added draw modes (only simple draw right now but the basic framework is there Added white rectangle to tileset canvas (surrounds selected tiles) Selected tiles canvas now changes zoom with tileset zoom (might remove this however) Multiple tile selection and drawing (undo/redo with this is somewhat slow Also started work on PXPACK save function (need to store all parts of file first though - haven't put in scroll types or "visibility" yet)
Renamed com.fdl to io.fdeitylink to more closely match my website domain

Improved tile placing on map Faster & more efficient Set bounds on x & y to avoid indexoutofboundsexceptions Fixed bug where if selected tiles would go off edge of map (eg horizontal len of 2 and click on last tile) no tiles would be placed
Cleanup Code efficiency Regenerated JavaDoc Rebuilt class files & jar Renamed "purple_check.png" to "purple_checkerboard.png"
Updated HackTab Disables invalid fields Private HackField class to better manage each item's attributes and editing Also NotepadTab class in KeroEdit now
Stopped ignoring out directory
Whoops - did it wrong - now actually stops ignoring .class & .jar files
Moved PxAttrManager class into io.fdeitylink.map package
Some license prompt refactoring
Replaced all uses of File objects with uses of Path objects and Files class
Updated jar build
Cleanup Realized JavaDocs weren't getting committed so I added them to Git

Created tileset and entity image central manager Works similarly to the PxAttrManager so there is only one instance of an Image object for a given tileset Also created ImageDimensions class that stores constants for dimensions of tilesets and the unittype.png image
Used try-with-resources wherever possible
Map description text now appears in tooltip on tab Cleanup - Changed how ScriptEditTab reads in lines - Realized not all referenced maps were being stored due to len diff in PxPack.Head constructor

Mostly cleanup GameData is safer when loading a mod or retrieving information Now using SimpleIntegerProperty with flags for displayedLayers instead of array of SimpleBooleanProperties Config now saves displayedLayers Changed how license is read in KeroEdit.showLicense() (Stream & Files.lines() instead of BufferedReader & Files.newBufferedReader())
Stored tilesets and pxattrs are wiped when a new mod is loaded And a tiny bit of cleanup
Refactored PxAttrManager and PxAttr so only one copy of mpt00 is stored When used as a default and an attribute needs to be changed, it is cloned into a new PxAttr, and the attribute is changed there
Made all concrete classes final
PxPack can save! woot! Improved error checking in PxPack constructor and PxPack.readString()
Improved error handling and exceptions in PxPack Better assurances on file and object validity

Severe improvement to error handling, exception strings Added wipe() to GameData - resets inst to null & invalidates until next valid call to init() Added NullArgumentException() - child of NullPointerException specifically for null arguments Cleanup

Cleanup & efficiency improvements Removed pointless/useless strings in messages.properties Logger fails silently All runtime exceptions should be logged now EnumMap filler! =D (using default interface methods and generics)
Cleanup Improved EnumMap retrieval Improved error handling Made setChanged() in FileEditTab final

MapEditTab and ScriptEditTab both save Prompts user about unsaved changes when tab is closed, new mod is loaded, or program is closed Removed reload in File menu - it was useless since Load Last can do essentially the same thing loadMod() fully handles any IOExceptions thrown during its execution (shows prompt to user) ScriptEditTab has two constructors, use depending on if called from KeroEdit or MapEditTab HackEditTab is now singleton (ish - singleton in the same way GameData is singleton) FileEditTab moved to FXUtil class Better error handling Cleanup and refactoring
Added multiple selection in script file chooser
Added multiple selection to the map list
Added UndoableMapResizeEdit to allow undoing a resize Cleanup

Added selected layer, draw mode to Config Cleanup Started work on integer flag for view settings (akin to displayed layers) Added emptyImage field to ImageManager class for when a loaded image is empty

Full use of viewSettings bitflags (akin to displayedLayers) that will function for tile types, grid, and entity boxes, sprites, and names Config saves view settings Removed KeroEdit.ViewSettingsItem enum as it was not being used Cleanup
PxAttr saves on attr change MapEditTab.PropertyEditTab now extends FXUtil.FileEditTab Cleanup
Added Grid view setting ScriptEditTab creates new file if it doesn't already exist Cleanup
Changed use of integer bitflags for displayedLayers & viewSettings to EnumSets Renamed ArrayIndexEnum to SafeOrdinalEnum Cleanup

Damn it, major changes/overhaul again Increased version number to v0.0.2 since there have been a ton of changes and KeroEdit is fairly functional now MapEditTab.PropertyEditTab can actually change values now, so the majority of the PXPACK Head can be changed Created util.fx package for utilities related to JavaFX Moved FileEditTab out of FXUtil class Created PoppableTab class intended for allowing the content of a Tab to be put into a floating stage and vice versa GameData uses ObservableLists to allow binding and using ChangeListeners GameData has getters for all lists Added more dimensions to ImageDimensions Moved PxAttr class out of PxAttrManager Allowed modifying PxAttr files - a "palette" is brought up when you right-click on a tile in MapEditTab.TileEditTab.TilesetPane Enabled entity sprite and box view settings so both can be drawn now Improved drag-select/multiple-selection on TilesetPane Made PxPack.rename() ensure proper filename length Added static final ints to PxPack class for maximum string lengths Made PxPack inner class toString() methods more clear and succinct with String.format() rather than long append() chains Made ResourceManager work properly for retrieving internal files when KeroEdit runs as a JAR by creating a new FileSystem Made note of exception in ScriptEditTab constructor that others have reported that I can't get myself Config stores whether or not tileset stage is showing Disabled HackTab for now If a script is open and the user wishes to open the script's map, the script will be properly closed Added FXUtil.task() and service() to allow constructing Tasks and Services using lambda expressions Added NullArgumentException.requireNonNull() (akin to Objects.requireNonNull(), but throws NullArgumentException, not NullPointerException) Improved error checking Cleanup

Replaced SafeOrdinalEnum with marker interface SafeEnum Also added AbstractSafeEnum class - this emulates the enum but it's cumbersome and has issues I can't reasonably solve Added OrderedMember annotation (used for AbstractSafeEnum) Removed ArrayUtil class Cleanup
Replaced FileEditTab.setChanged(boolean) with markChanged() and markUnchanged()
